♪ ♪

23:42.797 --> 23:49.053
♪ ♪

23:49.053 --> 23:50.597
- HEY.
THIS IS YOURS.

23:50.597 --> 23:52.181
- WOULD YOU MIND IF WE LEFT,
LIKE, RIGHT NOW?

23:52.181 --> 23:53.642
AND DON'T PRETEND LIKE YOU GIVE
A SHIT BECAUSE I SAW YOU

23:53.642 --> 23:54.976
OVER HERE
TEXTING YOUR BOYFRIEND.

23:54.976 --> 23:56.561
- WE JUST GOT HERE.

24:03.401 --> 24:05.529
HEY.

24:05.529 --> 24:07.530
WHAT HAPPENED?
- I'M NOT PROUD OF IT.

24:07.530 --> 24:09.031
- OKAY.

24:09.031 --> 24:10.408
- I WAS ON THE DANCE FLOOR
WITH THIS GUY.

24:10.408 --> 24:12.118
WE STARTED GETTING FRICTION
GOING.

24:12.118 --> 24:14.203
AND I HAD AN ORGASM.
I THOUGHT I SHOULD GET OUT

24:14.203 --> 24:15.788
OF THERE BEFORE HE STARTED
GETTING ANY IDEAS.

24:15.788 --> 24:17.582
- WAIT, YOU HAD AN--
- THAT'S HOW HORNY

24:17.582 --> 24:19.543
AND LONELY
I'VE BEEN THESE DAYS,

24:19.543 --> 24:21.377
LIKE A DOG
HUMPING A LAMPPOST.

24:21.377 --> 24:23.921
KEV GIVING ALL HIS LOVE
TO THOSE BABIES.

24:23.921 --> 24:25.549
DID I JUST CHEAT ON KEV?

24:25.549 --> 24:28.134
- IT WASN'T INTENTIONAL,
RIGHT?

24:28.134 --> 24:30.219
- I DIDN'T GO ON THE DANCE FLOOR
THINKING IT WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

24:30.219 --> 24:32.471
BUT ONCE THE GRINDING
STARTED, YEAH.

24:32.471 --> 24:34.765
THAT SHIT WAS INTENTIONAL.

24:34.765 --> 24:37.018
- SO WE HAD DIM SUM.

24:37.018 --> 24:38.561
THEN WHAT?

24:38.561 --> 24:41.314
- I-I HAD SO MANY PORK BUNS,
I HAD TO NAP IN THE CAR.

24:41.314 --> 24:42.315
- YOU AGAIN?

24:42.315 --> 24:43.482
- NO, WE'RE NOT EATING.

24:43.482 --> 24:44.483
WE'RE JUST CHECKING
THE PLACE--

24:44.483 --> 24:46.611
- READY FOR MORE?

24:46.611 --> 24:49.531
THIS WAY.

24:59.624 --> 25:00.666
- GAMBLING.

25:00.666 --> 25:02.835
GODDAMMIT.

25:02.835 --> 25:05.796
- DO YOU--DO YOU THINK
YOU LOST MONEY?

25:05.796 --> 25:06.964
- WELL,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

25:06.964 --> 25:09.050
SINCE I WOKE UP
WITH NOTHING.

25:09.050 --> 25:10.301
- THAT TABLE?

25:10.301 --> 25:12.219
THOUSAND-DOLLAR LIMIT.

25:12.219 --> 25:13.512
- NO, THANK YOU.

25:13.512 --> 25:16.682
- YOUR FRIEND IS EXPERT
AT PAI GOW.

25:24.106 --> 25:27.443
VERY AGGRESSIVE.

25:27.443 --> 25:30.029
ALMOST LOST EVERYTHING.

25:30.029 --> 25:34.408
THEN DOUBLE HIS MONEY.
[cheering]

25:34.408 --> 25:36.118
LEFT WITH THREE LADIES.

25:41.707 --> 25:43.710
VERY LUCKY GUY.
- YOU HEAR THAT?

25:43.710 --> 25:46.379
YOU DOUBLED YOUR MONEY.

25:46.379 --> 25:48.130
- I SAY WHERE I WAS GOING?

25:48.130 --> 25:49.340
- NO.

25:55.972 --> 26:00.851
[playing piano]

26:00.851 --> 26:03.270
[knocking]

26:06.774 --> 26:08.859
- HEY.
- HEY.

26:08.859 --> 26:10.653
I THOUGHT YOU WERE HANGING OUT
WITH YOUR FRIEND TONIGHT.

26:10.653 --> 26:12.655
- I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

26:22.289 --> 26:24.793
- WELL.

26:24.793 --> 26:26.795
UH, BEER?

26:33.509 --> 26:35.636
- I'M FALLING IN LOVE
WITH YOU, TOO.

26:37.680 --> 26:40.558
- OKAY.

26:40.558 --> 26:41.726
- IS IT?

26:49.817 --> 26:52.820
[rock music]

26:52.820 --> 26:59.160
♪ ♪

26:59.160 --> 27:01.328
- ♪ YEAH ♪

27:01.328 --> 27:04.915
♪ YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT ♪

27:04.915 --> 27:07.334
♪ YOU'RE SUCH A BIG SHOT,
BIG MOUTH ♪

27:07.334 --> 27:08.919
♪ AND THAT'S ALL
THAT YOU GOT ♪

27:08.919 --> 27:11.839
♪ YOU GOT, YOU GOT,
YOU GOT, YOU GOT ♪

27:11.839 --> 27:13.632
♪ YEAH ♪

27:13.632 --> 27:17.219
♪ WE AIN'T MESSING AROUND ♪

27:17.219 --> 27:18.804
♪ WE SPREAD LOVE,
DON'T KILL ♪

27:18.804 --> 27:21.307
♪ AND SHAKE SOME
SOLID GROUND ♪

27:21.307 --> 27:26.687
♪ SOME GROUND, SOME GROUND,
SOME GROUND, SOME GROUND ♪

27:26.687 --> 27:29.440
- GIRL BOXERS AT THE GYM
ARE IN SERIOUSLY GOOD SHAPE.

27:29.440 --> 27:31.233
MIGHT TAKE ME A FEW WEEKS
TO GET RIPPED LIKE THAT.

27:31.233 --> 27:32.818
- IF YOU WANT TO KNOW HOW TO
PUT ON SOME MUSCLE MASS,

27:32.818 --> 27:34.528
I'M YOUR GUY.

27:34.528 --> 27:37.531
BESIDES, MMA CHICKS
ARE SUPER HOT.

27:37.531 --> 27:40.034
IT MUST BE KIND OF WEIRD DATING
A CHICK WHO CAN KICK YOUR ASS.

27:40.034 --> 27:41.786
OH, GOOD MORNING, BABY.

27:41.786 --> 27:43.788
- HEY.
MORNING, DEBS.

27:43.788 --> 27:45.664
- HI, V.
I WAS JUST DROPPING LIAM OFF.

27:45.664 --> 27:48.209
SEE YOU, KEV.
- SEE YOU LATER, DEB.

27:48.209 --> 27:50.127
- YEAH. I SAID I'D WATCH LIAM
FOR A COUPLE HOURS.

27:50.127 --> 27:51.962
HOW WAS LAST NIGHT?
WAS IT FUN?

27:51.962 --> 27:53.798
- IT WAS FINE.
- YEAH?

27:53.798 --> 27:55.382
I'M SORRY I DIDN'T GO.

27:55.382 --> 27:56.884
- I BETTER GO OPEN THE BAR.
PROBABLY GUYS

27:56.884 --> 27:58.636
HUDDLED AROUND THE DOOR
WITH THE SHAKES.

27:58.636 --> 28:00.722
- ALL RIGHT.
SAY BYE TO MOMMY.

28:00.722 --> 28:03.015
SAY BYE TO THE GIRLS.

28:03.015 --> 28:04.225
BYE, MAMA.

28:04.225 --> 28:05.726
- BYE.

28:05.726 --> 28:07.144
- BYE, MAMA.

28:08.813 --> 28:10.981
[trilling]

28:10.981 --> 28:14.819
[phone ringing]

28:14.819 --> 28:17.154
- PATSY'S.
THIS IS MELINDA, CAN I HELP YOU?

28:17.154 --> 28:18.781
- HEY, AH, IT'S FIONA.

28:18.781 --> 28:20.574
I'M SCHEDULED
FOR A DOUBLE TODAY.

28:20.574 --> 28:22.827
BUT I'M JUST
NOT FEELING GREAT.

28:22.827 --> 28:24.871
I WAS WONDERING
IF IT'S NOT BUSY,

28:24.871 --> 28:25.955
MAYBE YOU DON'T NEED ME?

28:25.955 --> 28:28.792
AND YOU GUYS
CAN TAKE MY TABLES.

28:28.792 --> 28:30.459
- SEAN, IT'S FIONA.
SAYS SHE'S NOT FEELING--

28:30.459 --> 28:34.255
- NO, NO, NO, NO.
DON'T PUT SEAN ON.

28:34.255 --> 28:35.965
- YOU CAN'T MAKE
THE LUNCH SHIFT?

28:35.965 --> 28:37.842
- [gasps]
NO, NO.

28:37.842 --> 28:39.301
I CAN.
I CAN.

28:39.301 --> 28:41.720
I JUST THOUGHT
IF IT WASN'T BUSY--

28:41.720 --> 28:43.264
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
WELL, YOU'RE OFF THE HOOK.

28:43.264 --> 28:45.015
BUT I NEED YOU FOR DINNER.
- SURE.

28:45.015 --> 28:47.685
OKAY.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

28:51.272 --> 28:54.817
[rifling through drawers]

28:58.112 --> 29:03.033
- WHAT THE FUCK?
- MORNING.

29:03.033 --> 29:05.077
- WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?

29:05.077 --> 29:06.662
- OH, YOU MEAN THIS?

29:06.662 --> 29:08.664
IT WAS JUST SOMETHING
I THREW ON.

29:13.752 --> 29:15.629
- WHAT THE FUCK?
- OKAY.

29:15.629 --> 29:17.882
SO YOUR SUITCASE
GAVE ME AN IDEA, RIGHT?

29:17.882 --> 29:19.843
SO I WENT TO THE AIRPORT,
AND THEY EVEN HAVE

29:19.843 --> 29:21.177
UNCLAIMED BAGGAGE
JUST OFF TO THE SIDE

29:21.177 --> 29:22.970
JUST SITTING THERE.

29:22.970 --> 29:25.431
- ARE YOU WEARING MINK?
- NO, IT'S FAKE, BUT IT'S NICE.

29:25.431 --> 29:27.683
YES?
- NO. IT'S NOT NICE, LOOK.

29:27.683 --> 29:28.935
I HATE TO BURST
YOUR BUBBLES HERE.

29:28.935 --> 29:30.937
YOU BOTH LOOK
FUCKING INSANE.

29:30.937 --> 29:32.479
THIS ALL YOU GOT?

29:32.479 --> 29:37.776
- WE HAVE ELECTRIC SHAVERS,
JAMAICAN RUM, AND THIS.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.320
- OH.

29:39.320 --> 29:41.655
- THAT HAS A HAIR ON IT.
- WHAT? YOU DON'T WANT IT?

29:41.655 --> 29:44.033
- NO, I--YOU TOUCH ME
WITH THAT,

29:44.033 --> 29:45.826
I WILL KNOCK THE TEETH
OUT OF YOUR HEAD.

29:45.826 --> 29:48.579
I WILL KNOCK THE TEETH--
- EN GARDE.

29:48.579 --> 29:49.830
- WHAT THE FUCK
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

29:49.830 --> 29:51.832
- EN GARDE.
POW.

29:51.832 --> 29:55.753
- WHAT THE FUCK
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

29:55.753 --> 29:58.714
THIS IS NOT FUNNY.
I'M NOT FUCKING STAR WARS--

29:58.714 --> 30:00.799
- [laughs]

30:00.799 --> 30:02.927
- NO WAY.
A PORSCHE.

30:02.927 --> 30:05.137
- SHUT THE FUCK UP.

30:05.137 --> 30:07.015
- YOU GET
THE INSURANCE MONEY?

30:07.015 --> 30:09.099
- SAMMI CAN'T KNOW
ABOUT THIS.

30:09.099 --> 30:11.019
IS SHE AROUND?
- NO.

30:11.019 --> 30:13.145
SHE SAYS YOU
OWE HER AN RV.

30:13.145 --> 30:15.022
- SHIT.

30:15.022 --> 30:16.565
- CAN I GET A HUNDRED BUCKS?

30:16.565 --> 30:18.317
- DON'T HAVE IT.

30:18.317 --> 30:21.988
YOU KNOW IF I SNUCK BACK INTO
THE HOUSE NIGHT BEFORE LAST?

30:21.988 --> 30:25.157
HID SOMETHING
UNDER THE FLOORBOARDS, MAYBE,

30:25.157 --> 30:27.534
OR IN THE BACK YARD?

30:27.534 --> 30:29.620
- DON'T THINK SO.

30:29.620 --> 30:30.829
CAN I TAKE IT FOR A SPIN?

30:30.829 --> 30:32.957
- NO.

30:32.957 --> 30:36.585
- YOU HAVE A CREDIT CARD?

30:36.585 --> 30:38.462
- LET ME SEE THAT.

30:38.462 --> 30:41.590
- IT SAYS THE LOREN.

30:41.590 --> 30:44.635
- IT'S A HOTEL KEY.

30:44.635 --> 30:47.805
- CAN I JUST TELL YOU
HOW HAPPY I AM RIGHT NOW?

30:47.805 --> 30:49.723
- REALLY?
BECAUSE AT THE DINER YESTERDAY,

30:49.723 --> 30:51.809
I THOUGHT MAYBE
I WENT TOO FAR.

30:51.809 --> 30:53.895
- NO.

30:53.895 --> 30:56.981
YOU MAKE ME FEEL SANE.
- HMM?

30:56.981 --> 30:59.900
- AND I WANT TO BE AROUND YOU
ALL THE TIME,

30:59.900 --> 31:02.653
EVEN WHEN
WE'RE NOT FUCKING.

31:02.653 --> 31:04.363
I MEAN, NO.
WE'RE USUALLY FUCKING.

31:04.363 --> 31:05.990
BUT DURING THE BRIEF WINDOWS
OF TIME

31:05.990 --> 31:08.117
WHEN WE'RE DOING
OTHER THINGS BESIDES FUCKING,

31:08.117 --> 31:09.952
LIKE EATING PANCAKES
WITH OUR HANDS--

31:09.952 --> 31:13.580
- YOU WANT TO GET MARRIED?

31:13.580 --> 31:14.916
- WHAT?

31:14.916 --> 31:16.208
- I MEAN, MY FOLKS
MET ON A TUESDAY

31:16.208 --> 31:18.836
AND MARRIED TWO DAYS LATER.
- NO SHIT?

31:18.836 --> 31:21.505
- NO. MY DAD--HE WAS
SHIPPING OFF FOR VIETNAM--

31:21.505 --> 31:22.881
ASKED HER.
SHE SAID YES.

31:22.881 --> 31:24.591
- ARE THEY STILL TOGETHER?

31:24.591 --> 31:27.970
- YEAH.
STILL ARE.

31:27.970 --> 31:29.931
- I'D MARRY YOU.
- OH, WOULD YOU?

31:29.931 --> 31:31.473
- WHY? IS THERE A REASON
I SHOULDN'T?

31:31.473 --> 31:33.267
- NO. I'M A GOOD CHOICE.
- I'M A GREAT CHOICE.

31:33.267 --> 31:34.601
- WELL, IF IT WERE UP TO ME,
I'D DO IT TODAY.

31:34.601 --> 31:36.520
- DO IT RIGHT NOW.
- OH.

31:36.520 --> 31:39.732
ALL RIGHT.

31:39.732 --> 31:42.026
- [chuckles]

31:44.695 --> 31:45.989
- MARRIAGE IN CHICAGO.

31:45.989 --> 31:47.573
- YEP. ALL RIGHT.

31:47.573 --> 31:49.158
OPEN THAT.

31:49.158 --> 31:50.952
- WELL, SHOULD WE WAIT
TILL AFTER WE'RE MARRIED?

31:50.952 --> 31:52.870
- NO.
IT'S CRAP CHAMPAGNE.

31:52.870 --> 31:53.912
ALL RIGHT.
CHICAGO.

31:53.912 --> 31:55.664
SAME-DAY WEDDINGS.

31:55.664 --> 31:57.583
YOU CAN GET A MARRIAGE LICENSE
AT THE COURTHOUSE,

31:57.583 --> 31:59.043
GET MARRIED
IN THE SAME BUILDING.

31:59.043 --> 32:02.005
- DOWNLOAD APPLICATION
FOR WEDDING LICENSE.

32:02.005 --> 32:03.047
BOOM.

32:03.047 --> 32:05.883
- PRINT ONE?

32:05.883 --> 32:07.009
- WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?

32:07.009 --> 32:09.803
- ALL RIGHT.
- [laughs]

32:09.803 --> 32:11.638
- SLOW MOTION.

32:11.638 --> 32:12.848
HANDS RELAXED.

32:12.848 --> 32:15.017
FINGERS TOGETHER.

32:15.017 --> 32:17.853
SO AS YOU THROW THE HOOK,
YOU'RE GONNA ROTATE YOUR BODY

32:17.853 --> 32:19.855
UNTIL YOUR RIGHT HEEL
COMES OFF THE GROUND.

32:19.855 --> 32:21.148
GO AHEAD.

32:26.236 --> 32:27.863
OKAY.
NOW FASTER.

32:29.865 --> 32:32.701
- [grunting]

32:32.701 --> 32:35.788
- WHAT IS GOING ON?

32:35.788 --> 32:37.373
- I MIGHT NEED TO WORK
ON MY FORM.

32:48.967 --> 32:50.969
- I'M DIGGING
THE NAKED CLERICAL WORK.

32:50.969 --> 32:53.180
- ALL RIGHT.
SO HERE.

32:53.180 --> 32:56.642
WE JUST HAVE TO FILL THESE OUT,
TURN THEM IN AT THE COURTHOUSE.

32:56.642 --> 33:00.146
- OKAY, ARE YOU RELATED
TO APPLICANT A?

33:00.146 --> 33:02.773
WHO'S APPLICANT A?

33:02.773 --> 33:04.066
- THAT WOULD BE ME.

33:04.066 --> 33:06.318
- AM I RELATED TO YOU?

33:06.318 --> 33:09.988
I LOVE THAT THEY
HAVE TO ASK THAT.

33:09.988 --> 33:13.076
- UH, YOU'RE NOT GONNA
TAKE MY LAST NAME, ARE YOU?

33:13.076 --> 33:14.743
I'M--I'M--I MEAN,
I'M COOL EITHER WAY, BUT--

33:14.743 --> 33:16.578
- FENDER?
FIONA FENDER?

33:16.578 --> 33:18.122
WHY NOT?

33:18.122 --> 33:20.165
FIONA FENDER.

33:20.165 --> 33:22.709
- THAT WAS ACTUALLY A P
AT THE FRONT.

33:22.709 --> 33:24.461
- WHERE? COME ON.
- SERIOUSLY.

33:24.461 --> 33:27.131
IN FRONT OF THE F.
SEE?

33:27.131 --> 33:29.091
IT'S SILENT.
NOBODY EVER READS IT RIGHT.

33:29.091 --> 33:30.759
ACTUALLY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TAKE MY NAME.

33:30.759 --> 33:32.136
- NO, NO, NO.
I WANT TO.

33:32.136 --> 33:33.637
I WANT TO.

33:33.637 --> 33:35.722
FIONA P-FENDER.

33:35.722 --> 33:36.932
THAT'S--

33:36.932 --> 33:38.016
- THAT'S P-FUCKED UP.

33:38.016 --> 33:43.439
- IT'S P-FUCKING SEXY.
- MMM.

33:43.439 --> 33:45.441
- HEY, WHAT TIME IS IT?

33:45.441 --> 33:47.235
I'VE GOT TO BE AT WORK
AT P-FIVE,

33:47.235 --> 33:49.153
AND I CAN LOSE THIS P-JOB.
[laughs]

33:49.153 --> 33:51.155
- WELL, IF WE ARE GOING
TO SQUEEZE A WEDDING IN,

33:51.155 --> 33:52.198
WE HAVE GOT TO GET
A MOVE ON.

33:52.198 --> 33:54.200
COME ON.

34:00.581 --> 34:02.040
- WHOA.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.042
- THEY SAID I'M PAID UP
TILL TONIGHT.

34:04.042 --> 34:07.171
GUESS YOUR OLD MAN'S
GOT FANCY TASTE IN HOTEL ROOMS.

34:10.174 --> 34:12.426
AND CHINESE PROSTITUTES.

34:16.847 --> 34:19.641
'86 CHATEAU LAFITE ROTHSCHILD.

34:19.641 --> 34:21.810
HOW MUCH WAS THIS?
- $2,100.

34:21.810 --> 34:23.437
BUT YOU ORDER IT.

34:23.437 --> 34:25.063
YOU LEFT YOUR JACKET.

34:29.235 --> 34:32.280
- I ASSUME SINCE
YOU'RE HERE,

34:32.280 --> 34:33.614
I PAID IN ADVANCE?

34:33.614 --> 34:35.616
- THROUGH THE WEEKEND.

34:35.616 --> 34:37.075
SO IF YOU AND YOUR BOY

34:37.075 --> 34:38.619
WANT TO DO SOME--
- OKAY.

34:38.619 --> 34:41.205
TELL ME EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
WHEN YOU LAST SAW ME.

34:41.205 --> 34:43.207
- WE WERE PARTYING.

34:43.207 --> 34:44.708
- JUST US?

34:44.708 --> 34:47.628
[cheering]

34:47.628 --> 34:50.297
- AND SOME DENTISTS
YOU MET DOWNSTAIRS IN TOWN

34:50.297 --> 34:51.715
FOR THE CONVENTION.

34:56.512 --> 35:00.224
AND A GUY THAT WORKS OUT FRONT
AT THE HOT DOGS.

35:02.893 --> 35:06.063
AND A BUSINESSMAN
FROM DOWN THE HALL.

35:07.856 --> 35:10.901
YOU AND HIM LEFT TOGETHER.

35:10.901 --> 35:12.819
- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

35:12.819 --> 35:14.571
WHAT KIND OF BUSINESSMAN?

35:14.571 --> 35:16.240
- HE LEFT HIS CARD.

35:16.240 --> 35:17.366
- DIAMOND.

35:28.043 --> 35:29.295
- DIAMOND APPRECIATIONS.

35:29.295 --> 35:31.214
- YEAH.
IT'S FRANK GALLAGHER.

35:31.214 --> 35:32.298
I'M LOOKING FOR--

35:32.298 --> 35:34.132
- FRANK!
WHAT A NIGHT WE HAD.

35:34.132 --> 35:36.927
- YEAH.
ABOUT THAT--

35:36.927 --> 35:39.096
- I KNOW YOU'RE NERVOUS.

35:39.096 --> 35:41.932
LOT OF MONEY
TO HAND OVER TO A STRANGER.

35:41.932 --> 35:43.475
- HOW MUCH WAS IT AGAIN?

35:43.475 --> 35:45.310
- $113,000.

35:45.310 --> 35:46.979
BUT FRANK, TRUST ME.

35:46.979 --> 35:49.565
IT WAS THE BEST INVESTMENT
YOU COULD MAKE.

35:49.565 --> 35:51.942
- NO, NO, NO.
I NEVER DOUBTED IT.

35:51.942 --> 35:53.652
TELL ME,
HOW SOON DO YOU THINK--

35:53.652 --> 35:55.363
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING NOW?

35:55.363 --> 35:57.072
UH, YOU WANT TO COME
TO THE OFFICE? SEE FOR YOURSELF?

35:57.072 --> 36:00.576
- UH, GIVE ME THAT ADDRESS.

36:04.830 --> 36:06.832
- HAVE YOU DECLARED
A MAJOR, LIP?

36:06.832 --> 36:09.126
- ENGINEERING.

36:09.126 --> 36:11.044
- WELL,
YOU DIDN'T SEE THAT COMING.

36:11.044 --> 36:13.171
- OR MICROROBOTICS. YOU KNOW,
I HAVEN'T MADE UP MY MIND YET.

36:13.171 --> 36:14.464
- DAD'S AN ENGINEER.
HE INVENTED

36:14.464 --> 36:16.259
A LINE
OF WATER-FREE URINALS.

36:16.259 --> 36:18.386
- OH, REALLY?
- I DIDN'T INVENT THE URINALS.

36:18.386 --> 36:21.263
I, UH, WORKED ON THE SEALING
CARTRIDGE AND GASKET.

36:21.263 --> 36:22.973
THERE'S A LOT OF MONEY
IN URINE.

36:22.973 --> 36:25.892
IT NEVER GOES OUT OF FASHION.
- NICE.

36:25.892 --> 36:28.520
WHAT ARE YOU--
WHAT ARE YOU WORKING ON NOW?

36:28.520 --> 36:30.647
- PACKING MATERIALS.
- HE FILED A PATENT

36:30.647 --> 36:33.359
FOR A BIODEGRADABLE ALTERNATIVE
TO STYROFOAM.

36:33.359 --> 36:35.694
- OH. WHAT'S IT MADE OF?
- IT'S A TYPE OF FUNGI.

36:35.694 --> 36:37.405
- SMELLS LIKE MUSHROOMS.
- YOU TAKE

36:37.405 --> 36:39.531
ANY SUBSTRATE
OF INDUSTRIAL WASTE, LIKE--

36:39.531 --> 36:40.907
LIKE, UH,
CHOPPED-UP CORNSTALKS.

36:40.907 --> 36:44.077
AND YOU INJECT IT
WITH MYSELIUM,

36:44.077 --> 36:46.204
AND--SEE?
IT'S NOT VERY INTERESTING.

36:46.204 --> 36:48.249
- SO YOU JUST--
YOU POUR IT AROUND THE OBJECT

36:48.249 --> 36:49.416
THAT YOU'RE PACKING
AND THEN IT HARDENS?

36:49.416 --> 36:51.418
- THAT'S RIGHT.

36:51.418 --> 36:53.587
BECOMES A MOLD
OF THE OBJECT.

36:53.587 --> 36:54.921
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANT,

36:54.921 --> 36:57.799
I WILL SHOW YOU
MY WORKSHOP LATER.

36:57.799 --> 37:00.552
- SURE.
YEAH.

37:00.552 --> 37:03.347
[low background chatter]

37:03.347 --> 37:05.057
- I JUST, UH--
I JUST REALIZED THAT WE

37:05.057 --> 37:07.059
DON'T HAVE ANY WEDDING RINGS.
- THAT'S OKAY.

37:08.685 --> 37:10.228
- YEAH, I HAVE MY GRANDMA'S
ENGAGEMENT RING,

37:10.228 --> 37:11.772
BUT IT'S AT MY MOM'S HOUSE.

37:11.772 --> 37:16.234
DON'T WE NEED SOMETHING
FOR THE CEREMONY?

37:16.234 --> 37:17.319
OH, WAIT.

37:17.319 --> 37:19.322
FLOWERS.

37:22.949 --> 37:24.993
- 10 BUCKS FOR THOSE?
TRY 2.

37:26.787 --> 37:30.207
OH, LOOK.
RUBBER BANDS.

37:30.207 --> 37:31.792
THERE'S OUR WEDDING RINGS.

37:31.792 --> 37:33.293
I CAN MAKE A LITTLE CORSAGE.

37:33.293 --> 37:35.379
PUT A FLOWER
IN YOUR BUTTONHOLE.

37:35.379 --> 37:37.255
OH.
YOU DON'T HAVE A BUTTONHOLE.

37:37.255 --> 37:40.509
- I'LL JUST UNZIP MY FLY.

37:40.509 --> 37:42.386
- THIS IS STUPID, RIGHT?

37:42.386 --> 37:44.221
- RIGHT.

37:44.221 --> 37:46.349
- UNLESS IT'S NOT.

37:46.349 --> 37:48.600
- RIGHT?

37:48.600 --> 37:49.810
- I GOT TO BE AT WORK
IN AN HOUR.

37:49.810 --> 37:51.269
SHOULD WE JUST GO?

37:51.269 --> 37:52.562
- OKAY.

37:52.562 --> 37:54.564
- UNLESS WE SHOULDN'T.

37:54.564 --> 37:57.693
- GUS PFENDER
AND FIONA GALLAGHER.

38:05.451 --> 38:08.412
- PUT THAT SOMEPLACE SAFE.

38:08.412 --> 38:10.622
- ARE YOU GOOD WITH FRACTIONS?
- FRACTIONS OF WHAT?

38:10.622 --> 38:12.833
- LIKE IF YOU HAVE A 16th
OF AN OUNCE OF SOMETHING,

38:12.833 --> 38:15.043
HOW MANY GRAMS
WOULD THAT BE?

38:15.043 --> 38:17.170
- YOU DEALING DRUGS?
- NO.

38:17.170 --> 38:18.714
- IF FIONA FOUND
OUT I WAS HELPING YOU

38:18.714 --> 38:20.424
WITH YOUR DRUG FRACTIONS,
SHE'D HAVE MY SCALP.

38:20.424 --> 38:22.050
- NO ONE'S TELLING
FIONA ANYTHING.

38:22.050 --> 38:24.387
- BASIC OVERVIEW.
YOU GOT FLAPS,

38:24.387 --> 38:27.639
HALF G'S, G'S, TEENERS,
8 BALLS, AND OUNCES.

38:27.639 --> 38:31.309
AN OUNCE IS 28 GRAMS,
BUT REALLY IT'S 28.35.

38:31.309 --> 38:34.771
AN 8-BALL IS 3.54,
AND A TEENER IS 1.77.

38:34.771 --> 38:36.648
BUT THE DEALERS ROUND DOWN.

38:36.648 --> 38:39.609
SO THEY POCKET THE EXTRA 0.35.
YOU FOLLOWING?

38:39.609 --> 38:42.112
- I MIGHT NEED
TO WRITE THIS DOWN.

38:42.112 --> 38:45.407
[cheerful ballad]

38:45.407 --> 38:48.994
- ♪ THE TIMES WE HAD ♪

38:48.994 --> 38:52.205
♪ OH, WHEN THE WIND
WOULD BLOW ♪

38:52.205 --> 38:54.332
♪ WITH RAIN AND SNOW ♪

38:54.332 --> 38:57.461
♪ WERE NOT ALL BAD ♪

38:57.461 --> 39:01.840
♪ WE PUT OUR FEET
JUST WHERE THEY HAD ♪

39:01.840 --> 39:06.344
♪ HAD TO GO ♪

39:06.344 --> 39:11.808
♪ NEVER TO GO ♪

39:11.808 --> 39:15.396
♪ THE SHATTERED SOUL ♪

39:15.396 --> 39:20.358
♪ FOLLOWING CLOSE
BUT NEARLY TWICE AS SLOW ♪

39:20.358 --> 39:23.779
♪ IN MY GOOD TIMES ♪

39:23.779 --> 39:25.448
♪ THERE WERE ALWAYS
GOLDEN ROCKS TO THROW ♪

39:25.448 --> 39:26.615
- HOLY FUCK.

39:26.615 --> 39:28.825
- TOTALLY.

39:28.825 --> 39:30.702
- WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

39:30.702 --> 39:35.583
- I THINK I JUST
HAND THIS TO HIM TO SIGN.

39:35.583 --> 39:37.834
- HOLY FUCK.

39:37.834 --> 39:41.464
- ♪ THOSE WERE OUR TIMES ♪

39:41.464 --> 39:46.051
♪ THOSE WERE OUR TIMES ♪

39:46.051 --> 39:48.428
♪ ♪

39:48.428 --> 39:50.472
- I'M LOOKING
FOR DIAMOND APPRECIATIONS.

39:50.472 --> 39:52.057
CLEARLY,
I'M IN THE WRONG PLACE.

39:52.057 --> 39:54.059
MAYBE THERE'S AN OFFICE
UPSTAIRS OR--OR--

39:54.059 --> 39:55.769
- FRANK.

39:55.769 --> 39:58.146
- BUDDY?

39:58.146 --> 40:01.566
- NOW I UNDERSTAND
THIS WAS PERSONAL FOR YOU.

40:01.566 --> 40:04.861
THIS IS YOUR SON.
- YEAH.

40:04.861 --> 40:07.113
- WHAT'S YOUR NAME, MY FRIEND?
- CARL.

40:07.113 --> 40:09.741
- WHATEVER THE PROGNOSIS
IS FOR YOUR LEG,

40:09.741 --> 40:12.494
CARL, DO NOT DESPAIR.

40:12.494 --> 40:13.745
- IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

40:13.745 --> 40:15.997
- BRAVE BOY.

40:15.997 --> 40:17.541
I'M BUDDY DIAMOND.

40:17.541 --> 40:19.167
I FOUNDED THIS ORGANIZATION.

40:19.167 --> 40:21.586
- HOLD ON.
YOUR NAME IS DIAMOND?

40:21.586 --> 40:24.172
- COME THIS WAY.

40:24.172 --> 40:25.423
- [mouthing]
FUCK.

40:29.427 --> 40:31.012
- WHOA.

40:31.012 --> 40:34.349
- AS YOU KNOW,
MOST INSURANCE PLANS HAVE A CAP

40:34.349 --> 40:37.018
ON WHAT THEY'LL PAY
FOR PROSTHETIC LIMBS.

40:37.018 --> 40:41.273
BUT THANKS TO YOU,
THESE HOMELESS CHILDREN

40:41.273 --> 40:45.485
WILL LIVE NORMAL LIVES, PLAY
IN THE SCHOOL YARD, RIDE BIKES,

40:45.485 --> 40:47.028
RUN FOR THE SHEER JOY OF IT.

40:47.028 --> 40:50.115
KIDS, THIS IS THE MAN
I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

40:50.115 --> 40:51.449
THIS IS WHY YOU HAVE LEGS.

40:51.449 --> 40:55.621
[cheers and applause]

40:55.621 --> 40:57.540
- SUCH A--
SUCH A NOBLE ENTERPRISE.

40:57.540 --> 40:59.875
IT'S WONDERFUL WHAT YOU'RE DOING
FOR THESE KIDS.

40:59.875 --> 41:01.502
I AM SO MOVED BY IT.

41:01.502 --> 41:02.627
- I KNEW YOU WOULD BE.

41:02.627 --> 41:04.672
- BUT I NEED THE MONEY BACK.
- WHAT?

41:04.672 --> 41:06.756
- THERE'S BEEN A MISTAKE.
AND IT'S REGRETTABLE.

41:06.756 --> 41:09.759
AND WHILE I WOULD PREFER CASH,
I'LL TAKE A CHECK.

41:09.759 --> 41:11.261
- THE MONEY'S BEEN SPENT.

41:11.261 --> 41:12.679
THAT'S WHAT I BROUGHT YOU HERE
TO SEE.

41:12.679 --> 41:14.472
- NO, NO.
I NEED THAT MONEY BACK.

41:14.472 --> 41:15.765
- IT'S NOT POSSIBLE.
FRANK,

41:15.765 --> 41:18.226
YOU PAID FOR HALF
A DOZEN PROSTHETICS,

41:18.226 --> 41:19.811
INCLUDING THIS BEAUTY HERE

41:19.811 --> 41:24.566
WITH SILICONE SKIN
THAT GOES FOR $60,000.

41:24.566 --> 41:28.820
- ONE LEG? 60 GRAND?

41:28.820 --> 41:30.697
- HEY. HEY.
THAT DOESN'T BELONG TO YOU.

41:30.697 --> 41:32.073
- NO, NO.
- GIVE ME BACK MY LEG.

41:32.073 --> 41:33.617
GIVE IT BACK.
- THIS IS NOT YOUR LEG.

41:33.617 --> 41:34.784
- DON'T TAKE MY LEG.
- NO.

41:34.784 --> 41:36.995
THIS IS--NO.
[children yelling]

41:36.995 --> 41:39.080
I PAID FOR THE DAMN LEG.

41:39.080 --> 41:40.790
THAT'S ALL THE MONEY
I'VE GOT IN THE WORLD.

41:40.790 --> 41:44.336
THIS IS MY INSURANCE SETTLEMENT.
GOT TO GET MY MONEY BACK.

41:53.762 --> 41:56.724
- YOU WORK OUT A LOT.
- YEAH.

41:56.724 --> 41:58.559
PRO BOXERS TRAIN FOUR TO SIX
HOURS A DAY.

41:58.559 --> 42:00.727
- ARE YOU PRO?
- NAH.

42:00.727 --> 42:02.688
BUT I CAME IN THIRD LAST YEAR
IN ALL-CITY.

42:02.688 --> 42:04.397
- HOW'D YOU GET INTO BOXING?

42:04.397 --> 42:07.317
- WHEN I WAS 10, MY DAD
BEAT MY MOM UP REALLY BAD.

42:07.317 --> 42:09.569
WANTED TO BE ABLE TO DEFEND HER,
SO I STARTED TRAINING.

42:09.569 --> 42:12.656
- REALLY?

42:12.656 --> 42:15.408
- NO.

42:15.408 --> 42:19.746
ARE YOU GONNA STICK
WITH IT?

42:19.746 --> 42:22.332
- THINK SO.

42:27.045 --> 42:29.965
- [whistles]

42:29.965 --> 42:31.925
- ALL THAT MONEY.

42:31.925 --> 42:36.096
ALL THAT FUCKING MONEY
WASTED ON CHILD AMPUTEES,

42:36.096 --> 42:38.390
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.

42:38.390 --> 42:40.058
THERE'S A LESSON HERE, SON.

42:40.058 --> 42:42.644
CHARITY IS ACCEPTING HELP
FROM OTHERS,

42:42.644 --> 42:46.774
NOT THE OTHER WAY AROUND.
- OKAY.

42:46.774 --> 42:49.401
- AND TAKING PRESCRIPTION
MEDICATIONS WHILE DRINKING

42:49.401 --> 42:51.319
AND THEN SMOKING POT

42:51.319 --> 42:54.823
AND THEN SMOKING CRACK CAN LEAD
TO QUESTIONABLE DECISIONS.

42:54.823 --> 42:56.700
- CAN WE GET OUT OF HERE?
- I GOT TO GET THAT IMAGE

42:56.700 --> 42:59.369
OUT OF MY HEAD
OF THAT GIRL HOPPING AFTER ME.

42:59.369 --> 43:00.663
HOP, HOP, HOP, HOP.

43:00.663 --> 43:02.247
- AT LEAST
YOU STILL GOT THE CAR.

43:02.247 --> 43:05.875
- AND A HALF A BOTTLE
OF MASSIVELY OVERPRICED WINE.

43:05.875 --> 43:07.961
- IT'S THAT GUY.
LET'S GO.

43:07.961 --> 43:09.379
- DAD?
- HMM?

43:09.379 --> 43:10.505
- YOU KNOW THEM?

43:10.505 --> 43:12.465
- WHO?

43:12.465 --> 43:14.634
[grunts]
JESUS CHRIST!

43:14.634 --> 43:16.511
- GET OFF HIM.

43:16.511 --> 43:19.639
- I GAVE THE LEG BACK.
- WHAT LEG?

43:19.639 --> 43:23.059
- OKAY, WHOA, HOLD--WHAT--JUST--
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT AGAIN?

43:23.059 --> 43:24.686
- DEMITRI.
HE WORKS WITH US.

43:24.686 --> 43:26.688
AND YOU RAN HIM OVER WITH
THIS PORSCHE TWO NIGHTS AGO.

43:26.688 --> 43:28.523
- OH GEEZ.
- HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

43:28.523 --> 43:30.776
FULL BODY CAST.
[speaking Greek]

43:30.776 --> 43:32.193
THEY'RE CALLING THE COPS.
- WAIT.

43:32.193 --> 43:33.820
COME ON.
WE CAN WORK THIS OUT.

43:33.820 --> 43:34.904
- YOU PAY HIS MEDICAL BILLS?

43:34.904 --> 43:36.698
- OF COURSE.

43:36.698 --> 43:38.783
WELL, EVENTUALLY. I'M A LITTLE
TIGHT ON CASH RIGHT NOW.

43:38.783 --> 43:41.119
- CALL.
- OKAY. STOP. MY CAR.

43:41.119 --> 43:42.370
MY SWEET CAR.

43:42.370 --> 43:43.955
HUH?
WHAT ABOUT THAT?

43:43.955 --> 43:46.374
- IT'S FUCKED UP
FROM WHERE YOU HIT DEMITRI.

43:46.374 --> 43:49.837
- NO. COME--WITH A LITTLE PAINT
AND SOME BONDO,

43:49.837 --> 43:52.172
IT'S GOOD AS NEW.

43:53.923 --> 43:55.842
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

44:09.773 --> 44:11.149
- OH, TABLE SEVEN'S
READY TO ORDER.

44:11.149 --> 44:12.776
TABLE FIVE NEEDS A SALAD.

44:12.776 --> 44:15.528
- OH, SHIT. SORRY.
- YOU OKAY?

44:15.528 --> 44:17.781
I KNOW YOU WEREN'T
FEELING WELL.

44:17.781 --> 44:19.532
- UPSET STOMACH.
I'M FEELING BETTER.

44:19.532 --> 44:20.909
- I'LL GET TABLE SEVEN
FOR YOU.

44:20.909 --> 44:24.370
- THANKS.

44:24.370 --> 44:25.955
OH, YOU WANTED SODA.

44:25.955 --> 44:27.749
COMING UP.

44:27.749 --> 44:30.878
- HEY.

44:30.878 --> 44:31.961
- [laughing]
- HOW'S IT GOING?

44:31.961 --> 44:35.256
- GOOD.
- COME HERE, YOU OLD DOG.

44:35.256 --> 44:37.718
- YOU BETTER TELL YOUR BOYFRIEND
AND HIS BUDDIES TO CUT IT OUT.

44:37.718 --> 44:39.177
OTHERWISE,
THEY'RE GONNA HAVE TO GO.

44:39.177 --> 44:40.846
- SORRY.

44:40.846 --> 44:41.888
OKAY, ROCKERS.

44:41.888 --> 44:43.389
YOU CAN'T JUST BE SITTING--

44:43.389 --> 44:44.808
[acid rock chords]

44:44.808 --> 44:46.434
- ♪ HERE COMES THE BRIDE ♪

44:46.434 --> 44:49.187
[distorted singing]

44:49.187 --> 44:55.693
♪ DAH DAH-DAH DAH
DAH-DAH DAH DAH-DAH ♪

44:55.693 --> 44:58.822
- LADIES--LADIES
AND GENTLEMEN, OUR BASS PLAYER

44:58.822 --> 45:02.617
WENT OFF AND GOT MARRIED TODAY
TO THIS BEAUTIFUL WOMAN.

45:02.617 --> 45:03.952
SO THIS IS THEIR HONEYMOON,
SO WE'RE GONNA

45:03.952 --> 45:05.578
MAKE A LITTLE BIT OF NOISE.

45:05.578 --> 45:07.789
PLEASE WELCOME THE NEWLYWEDS,
GUS AND FIONA.

45:07.789 --> 45:11.960
[cheers and applause]

45:11.960 --> 45:19.300
- ♪ DAH DAH DAH-DAH
DAH DAH DAH DAH ♪

45:19.300 --> 45:21.427
[whistles]
[cheers and applause]

45:21.427 --> 45:25.807
- OKAY, THIS IS
AN ELECTRIC CAR

45:25.807 --> 45:27.809
THAT FOLDS INTO ITSELF

45:27.809 --> 45:31.521
SO IT CAN FIT AND PARK
IN TIGHT SPACES.

45:31.521 --> 45:33.231
- THAT'S NICE.
- YEAH. THE WHEELS,

45:33.231 --> 45:36.860
THEY TURN SEPARATELY SO YOU CAN
ROTATE AND STAY IN ONE SPOT.

45:36.860 --> 45:38.444
GUESS WHERE THE MOTOR IS.

45:38.444 --> 45:40.655
- WELL, IT'S NOT IN THE BACK,
RIGHT?

45:40.655 --> 45:42.490
AND DOES IT HAVE AIR BAGS?

45:42.490 --> 45:44.910
- YEP.

45:44.910 --> 45:48.496
- WELL, IT'S NOT
IN THE FRONT EITHER.

45:48.496 --> 45:51.959
WAIT, ARE--ARE--ARE THE ENGINES
IN THE WHEELS?

45:51.959 --> 45:53.877
- YES. THERE'S ONE
IN EACH WHEEL.

45:53.877 --> 45:55.587
- THAT'S VERY FUCKING COOL.

45:55.587 --> 45:57.547
- WE'RE OUT BY THE POOL
DRINKING COCKTAILS.

45:57.547 --> 45:58.840
- UH, YEAH. YEAH.
I'LL BE THERE IN A MINUTE.

45:58.840 --> 46:00.884
IS THAT OKAY?
- OKAY, NOW THIS--

46:00.884 --> 46:03.344
THIS WAS AN ATTEMPT
TO MAKE A PLASTIC FILM

46:03.344 --> 46:04.888
THAT'S ELECTRICALLY ACTIVE.

46:04.888 --> 46:06.849
AND I STILL HAVEN'T GOTTEN
IT TO WORK YET.

46:06.849 --> 46:08.641
- ARE YOU GUYS
ACTUALLY BONDING?

46:08.641 --> 46:10.226
I'M NOT SURE
I'M COMFORTABLE WITH THAT.

46:10.226 --> 46:11.853
- WE'RE ONLY DOING IT
TO ANNOY YOU, HONEY.

46:11.853 --> 46:14.564
OKAY, COME. CHECK THIS OUT.
- YEAH. YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

46:14.564 --> 46:18.818
JUST ONE MINUTE.

46:21.029 --> 46:22.572
YOU STILL HAVE TO HEAT
AND TREAT IT, RIGHT?

46:22.572 --> 46:23.907
- YEAH, TO KILL THE SPORES
AND DRY IT OUT.

46:23.907 --> 46:26.994
NOW DESPITE MY DAUGHTER'S
GIVING ME SHIT,

46:26.994 --> 46:28.453
IT DOES NOT SMELL
LIKE MUSHROOMS.

46:28.453 --> 46:30.663
IT IS, HOWEVER,

46:30.663 --> 46:34.167
A GOOD HIDING PLACE.
- SHIT.

46:34.167 --> 46:37.253
- NOW I ASSUME,
AS A YOUNG DELINQUENT,

46:37.253 --> 46:38.671
YOU SMOKE POT?
- MM-HMM.

46:38.671 --> 46:40.298
YEAH, WHEN I'M NOT
SHOOTING SMACK.

46:47.305 --> 46:48.974
- WHAT COURSES YOU TAKING?

46:48.974 --> 46:50.600
- THERMODYNAMICS.
YOU KNOW,

46:50.600 --> 46:52.435
I REALLY WANT TO GET INTO THE
AEROSPACE ENGINEERING

46:52.435 --> 46:53.770
PROGRAM AT SCHOOL.

46:53.770 --> 46:56.105
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
THIS SUMMER?

46:56.105 --> 46:59.985
- CONSTRUCTION, DEMO.
IN CHICAGO.

46:59.985 --> 47:03.196
YOU KNOW, I'M PRETTY MUCH JUST
HAULING CEMENT IN A WHEELBARROW.

47:03.196 --> 47:06.241
- WHY?

47:06.241 --> 47:08.534
- 'CAUSE IT'S A JOB.

47:08.534 --> 47:10.954
- NEXT TIME,
I'LL GET YOU A PAID INTERNSHIP.

47:10.954 --> 47:13.915
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE HEADED
FOR A SERIOUS CAREER, RIGHT?

47:17.043 --> 47:18.044
- HERE YOU GO.

47:18.044 --> 47:22.715
AH, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

47:22.715 --> 47:26.970
A BEER FOR MY HUSBAND.

47:26.970 --> 47:28.763
[laughter]

47:30.348 --> 47:31.934
- HEY, GO ON HOME.
WE GOT THIS.

47:31.934 --> 47:33.017
- BUT I'VE GOT THREE TABLES,

47:33.017 --> 47:35.020
AND THE TIPS
RIGHT NOW ARE SO GOOD.

47:35.020 --> 47:36.980
- NOW I GOT WHY YOU
WANTED THE SHIFT COVERED.

47:36.980 --> 47:40.984
FROM NOW ON, ANY TIME
YOU GET MARRIED, TAKE THE DAY.

47:40.984 --> 47:42.902
- IT'S NOT A JOKE.

47:42.902 --> 47:45.948
- FIONA PFENDER.
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

47:45.948 --> 47:47.657
- WHEN YOU GO FOR IT,
YOU REALLY GO FOR IT.

47:47.657 --> 47:49.033
- IT'S CRAZY, RIGHT?
I DON'T KNOW.

47:49.033 --> 47:50.953
IT--IT SEEMS RIGHT.

47:50.953 --> 47:53.579
- HE'S GREAT.
WE'RE REALLY HAPPY FOR YOU.

47:53.579 --> 47:57.208
- SURE WE ARE.
- [laughing]

47:57.208 --> 48:00.295
- JUST DON'T LIE ABOUT IT
NEXT TIME, OKAY?

48:00.295 --> 48:05.050
[phone ringing]
- HEY.

48:05.050 --> 48:06.509
- HEY.
YOU COMING HOME TONIGHT?

48:06.509 --> 48:08.553
- EVERYTHING OKAY?
- EVERYTHING'S FINE.

48:08.553 --> 48:11.097
JUST WANTED TO LET YOU KNOW
I AM NOT GOING ON THE PILL.

48:11.097 --> 48:12.765
- WHY NOT?
- I LOOKED IT UP.

48:12.765 --> 48:14.059
THE PILL REDUCES
MUSCLE MASS,

48:14.059 --> 48:15.643
AFFECTS MOOD
AND WATER RETENTION.

48:15.643 --> 48:17.395
PROBABLY NOT A GOOD IDEA NOW
THAT I'M TRAINING.

48:17.395 --> 48:18.730
- TRAINING FOR WHAT?

48:18.730 --> 48:19.981
- AW, I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

48:19.981 --> 48:21.107
YOU AT WORK?

48:21.107 --> 48:22.734
- YEAH.

48:22.734 --> 48:24.652
TODAY WAS--

48:24.652 --> 48:28.448
- WHAT?

48:28.448 --> 48:29.782
- I'LL BE HOME
IN THE MORNING, OKAY?

48:29.782 --> 48:31.076
CAN YOU--CAN YOU WATCH LIAM
FOR ME?

48:31.076 --> 48:32.119
TELL HIM I LOVE HIM?

48:32.119 --> 48:33.494
- YEAH, ABSOLUTELY. BYE.

48:33.494 --> 48:35.496
- BYE.

48:41.086 --> 48:42.587
- WHAT THE FUCK IS THIS?

48:42.587 --> 48:44.505
- IT'S MORE SUITCASES.
WE GOT DRESS SHIRTS,

48:44.505 --> 48:45.882
SHOES, SWEATERS,
PRETTY MUCH EVERYTHING

48:45.882 --> 48:47.425
- WAIT, YOU WENT BACK
TO THE AIRPORT?

48:47.425 --> 48:48.468
- YEAH, WHY NOT?
- 'CAUSE IT'S FUCKING RISKY

48:48.468 --> 48:50.095
IS WHY NOT.

48:50.095 --> 48:51.304
MOST OF THIS AIN'T
WORTH SHIT ANYWAY.

48:51.304 --> 48:53.014
IT'S OLD CLOTHES
AND FUCKING HAIR DRYERS.

48:53.014 --> 48:54.974
- HAIR DRYERS. YEAH. WE GOT
TOILETRIES OVER HERE, OKAY?

48:54.974 --> 48:56.851
- ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?
THERE'S BETTER WAYS TO MAKE

48:56.851 --> 48:58.020
MONEY, MAN.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

48:58.020 --> 48:59.520
- [muttering to himself]

48:59.520 --> 49:01.522
- WHY YOU PUTTING EVERYTHING
ON THE FUCKING PORCH?

49:03.232 --> 49:05.777
- WHY ARE THERE BOOTS
IN THE SNEAKERS PILE?

49:05.777 --> 49:08.488
WE GOT TO KEEP
THIS ORGANIZED, OKAY?

49:08.488 --> 49:10.573
WHERE ARE THE BELTS?

49:10.573 --> 49:11.908
I THOUGHT
I PUT THEM THERE.

49:11.908 --> 49:15.037
OBVIOUSLY,
THEY'VE BEEN MOVED.

49:15.037 --> 49:16.704
- YOUR BOYFRIEND'S LOSING
HIS SHIT.

49:16.704 --> 49:21.584
- MICKEY, HELP ME KEEP
THIS ORGANIZED, OKAY?

49:25.130 --> 49:26.089
- OH, HEY, BABE.
- HEY.

49:26.089 --> 49:27.423
- WHAT?
DID YOU WORK A DOUBLE?

49:27.423 --> 49:29.175
- PACO GOT SICK.

49:29.175 --> 49:30.635
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

49:30.635 --> 49:32.012
- OH, MY GOSH.

49:32.012 --> 49:34.263
SO AMY LOOKS UP AT ME
AND SAYS, "DA."

49:34.263 --> 49:35.556
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?

49:35.556 --> 49:36.933
MY LITTLE BABY GIRL.

49:36.933 --> 49:39.060
SHE'S HALFWAY TO DADA.

49:39.060 --> 49:41.063
- LAST NIGHT, I HAD AN ORGASM
WITH A STRANGER

49:41.063 --> 49:43.856
ON THE DANCE FLOOR.
- YOU HAD AN ORGASM?

49:43.856 --> 49:46.859
- GRINDING ON THE DANCE FLOOR.
- WAIT.

49:46.859 --> 49:49.071
BUT NOT--NOT LIKE A--
NOT LIKE--

49:49.071 --> 49:50.446
LIKE--LIKE--
LIKE A REAL ORGASM.

49:50.446 --> 49:52.074
YOU MEAN, LIKE,
YOU JUST HAD A GOOD TIME?

49:52.074 --> 49:54.158
- NO, I MEAN A REAL ORGASM
WITH ANOTHER MAN.

49:54.158 --> 49:56.078
IT DIDN'T EVEN TAKE
A WHOLE SONG.

49:56.078 --> 49:57.787
THAT'S HOW HORNY I AM.

49:57.787 --> 50:00.373
USED TO BE I COULD DRY HUMP FOR
45 MINUTES BEFORE GETTING OFF.

50:00.373 --> 50:02.291
NOW IT'S TWO GRINDS.

50:04.919 --> 50:06.921
YOU KNOW WHAT
THAT ORGASM WAS?

50:06.921 --> 50:08.840
THAT WAS A CRY FOR HELPFROME

50:08.840 --> 50:10.967
SAYING THINGS
AIN'T RIGHT AT HOME.

50:10.967 --> 50:13.970
[mellow guitar]

50:13.970 --> 50:16.431
♪ ♪

50:16.431 --> 50:20.143
- ♪ NEVER MADE A SUMMER ♪

50:20.143 --> 50:25.523
♪ OH, YOU KNOW
IT CAN'T BE FOUND ♪

50:25.523 --> 50:29.193
♪ YOUTH IS ALWAYS PRETTY ♪

50:29.193 --> 50:33.322
♪ OH, YOU KNOW
IT CAN'T BE FOUND ♪

50:33.322 --> 50:35.867
♪ WHAT YOU'VE SEEN ♪

50:35.867 --> 50:38.119
♪ ALL OVER ♪

50:38.119 --> 50:40.288
♪ YOU'LL HEAR IT ♪

50:40.288 --> 50:42.249
♪ ALL OVER ♪

50:42.249 --> 50:44.834
♪ AND YOU'LL FEEL IT ♪

50:44.834 --> 50:46.711
♪ ALL OVER ♪

50:46.711 --> 50:52.383
♪ AND YOU'LL KNOW
IT'S ME ♪

50:52.383 --> 50:55.137
♪ HE'S IN BAD CONDITION ♪

50:55.137 --> 50:56.262
- I'LL CLEAN UP.
- OH, OKAY.

50:56.262 --> 51:01.225
- ♪ HIDING IN THE HANDS
ALL DAY ♪

